main event: A civilian radar operator tracked several unidentified targets at 25,000 feet, traveling at high speeds of around 2,000 knots in Terre Haute, Indiana on 9/29/59.
interesting points: The targets were observed on radar for about 4 minutes and then went off the screen, indicating high-speed and maneuverable behavior.
The witness, a competent and experienced radar operator, lends significance to the report.
The USAF's SAFOI-34 file listed the incident as a case of 'possible equipment malfunction', despite the radar operator's observations.
An unidentified flying object sighting by a civilian was reported to the U.S. Air Force with no official conclusions reached as to their cause.
A president of Research and Studies Committee on Aerial Phenomena observed unusual lights and maneuvering fireballs in the sky on multiple occasions.
sighted object: multiple unidentified high-speed targets on radar, unusual lights, and fireballs in the sky
witnesses: civilian radar operator, president of Research and Studies Committee on Aerial Phenomena, pilot
